ctions, and UI actions must be echoed back into chat.\ndocs/product-brief.md:43:- Left pane is the chat workspace, about one-third width.\ndocs/product-brief.md:46:### Chat and UI Bridge\ndocs/product-brief.md:48:- User chat can propose structured actions such as selecting a tone or refining beats.\ndocs/product-brief.md:50:- Direct UI actions must create compact chat-visible summaries for auditability and replay.\ndocs/product-brief.md:56:- The system should periodically summarize what it is writing in chat.\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:15:    ChatIntentParsedEventPayload,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:16:    ChatMessageRecordedEventPayload,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:17:    ChatMessageRole,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:34:from app.models.intent_parser import ParsedChatIntentResponse\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:257:    def record_chat_message(\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:261:        message_role: ChatMessageRole,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:265:        source: str = \"chat\",\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:271:            actor=actor or _default_actor_for_chat_role(message_role),\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:272:            event_type=SessionEventType.CHAT_MESSAGE_RECORDED,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:273:            summary=f\"Recorded {message_role.value} chat message.\",\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:275:            payload=ChatMessageRecordedEventPayload(\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:284:    def record_chat_intent_parsed(\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:298:        result: ParsedChatIntentResponse,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:304:            summary = \"Parsed chat intent without actionable UI changes.\"\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:306:            summary = \"Parsed chat intent into 1 proposed action.\"\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:308:            summary = f\"Parsed chat intent into {action_count} proposed actions.\"\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:313:            event_type=SessionEventType.CHAT_INTENT_PARSED,\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:316:            payload=ChatIntentParsedEventPayload(\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:445:def _default_actor_for_chat_role(message_role: ChatMessageRole) -> SessionEventActor:\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:446:    if message_role == ChatMessageRole.USER:\nbackend/app/services/event_log.py:448:    if message_role == ChatMessageRole.ASSISTANT:\ndocs/README.md:10:- `chat-to-ui-actions.md`: proposed action contract, action catalog, default confirmation policy, and deterministic action-policy evaluator\ndocs/README.md:11:- `chat-action-echoes.md`: transcript echo rules, durable wiring, and compact summary guidelines for UI and chat actions\ndocs/README.md:12:- `chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json`: machine-readable schema bundle for chat-to-UI proposed actions\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/primitives.test.tsx:37:        label=\"Chat message\"\nfrontend/src/shared/ui/primitives.test.tsx:41:    const textarea = screen.getByLabelText('Chat message')\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:5:UI-to-chat coherence, and later real-time fan-out without relying on browser-only state.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:15:  - `user`: direct user actions from chat or UI.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:32:| `chat.message.recorded` | User, assistant, or system chat/history entry. | varies | optional |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:94:- `record_chat_message(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:152:  `summary_text` so later prompts, summaries, and chat replay can stay grounded\nprompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.yolopilot.md:12403:    - Collaborate through both chat and direct UI controls.\nprompts/08-repo-quality-tooling.yolopilot.md:12425:    Each stage must be durable, resumable, and editable. Chat messages can propose actions in the workflow, and direct UI actions must also be reflected back into the session chat log as compact summaries.\nprompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:13:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_6\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,240p' frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"import { Link, useParams } from 'react-router-dom'\\nimport { routePaths } from '../../app/routePaths.ts'\\nimport { workflowStageDefinitions } from '../../features/session/workflowStages.ts'\\n\\nconst chatRailPreview = [\\n  'Conversation history and quick actions will live in the left rail.',\\n  'UI actions will echo back into chat as compact structured messages.',\\n  'Agent summaries during composition and audio jobs will dock here.',\\n] as const\\n\\nexport function SessionWorkspacePage() {\\n  const { sessionId = 'unknown-session' } = useParams()\\n\\n  return (\\n    <section\\n      className=\\\"workspace-page\\\"\\n      aria-label={`Session workspace for ${sessionId}`}\\n    >\\n      <header className=\\\"workspace-page__header\\\">\\n        <div>\\n          <p className=\\\"eyebrow\\\">Session workspace</p>\\n          <h1>Session {sessionId}</h1>\\n          <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">\\n            This route-scoped shell reserves the left pane for chat and the\\n            right pane for the structured workflow UI.\\n          </p>\\n        </div>\\n\\n        <Link className=\\\"ghost-link\\\" to={routePaths.home}>\\n          Back to sessions\\n        </Link>\\n      </header>\\n\\n      <div className=\\\"workspace-shell\\\" data-testid=\\\"workspace-route\\\">\\n        <aside className=\\\"panel workspace-pane workspace-pane--chat\\\">\\n          <div className=\\\"pane-heading\\\">\\n            <h2>Chat lane</h2>\\n            <span className=\\\"status-chip\\\">1/3 width target</span>\\n          </div>\\n          <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">\\n            The left rail is reserved for conversation, quick actions, and\\n            durable chat history.\\n          </p>\\n\\n          <ol className=\\\"placeholder-list\\\">\\n            {chatRailPreview.map((entry) => (\\n              <li key={entry}>{entry}</li>\\n            ))}\\n          </ol>\\n        </aside>\\n\\n        <section className=\\\"panel workspace-pane workspace-pane--canvas\\\">\\n          <div className=\\\"pane-heading\\\">\\n            <h2>Workflow canvas</h2>\\n            <span className=\\\"status-chip\\\">Route param bound</span>\\n          </div>\\n          <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">\\n            The workspace already keys itself off the session route so future\\n            data loaders, stores, and websocket subscriptions can stay\\n            session-specific.\\n          </p>\\n\\n          <dl className=\\\"workspace-meta\\\">\\n            <div>\\n              <dt>Session ID</dt>\\n              <dd>{sessionId}</dd>\\n            </div>\\n            <div>\\n              <dt>Active route</dt>\\n              <dd>{`/sessions/${sessionId}`}</dd>\\n            </div>\\n            <div>\\n              <dt>Next prompt</dt>\\n              <dd>Two-pane workflow layout</dd>\\n            </div>\\n          </dl>\\n\\n          <ol className=\\\"workspace-stage-list\\\">\\n            {workflowStageDefinitions.map((stage, index) => (\\n              <li key={stage.id}>\\n                <span>{index + 1}</span>\\n                <div>\\n                  <strong>{stage.label}</strong>\\n                  <p>{stage.description}</p>\\n                </div>\\n              </li>\\n            ))}\\n          </ol>\\n        </section>\\n      </div>\\n    </section>\\n  )\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nprompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:74:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_38\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"find tools/webapp-qa/examples -maxdepth 2 -type f | sort | xargs -I {} sh -c 'echo \\\\\\\"--- {}\\\\\\\"; sed -n \\\\\\\"1,220p\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"{}\\\\\\\"'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"--- tools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage-workflow-contract.spec.json\\n{\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://frontend:8566\\\",\\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/homepage-workflow-contract.png\\\",\\n  \\\"viewport\\\": {\\n    \\\"width\\\": 1440,\\n    \\\"height\\\": 960\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForSelector\\\",\\n      \\\"selector\\\": \\\"[data-testid='app-card']\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Story studio path\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Story setup\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Running in frontend-only mode.\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Offline\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"screenshot\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n--- tools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json\\n{\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://frontend:8566\\\",\\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/homepage.png\\\",\\n  \\\"viewport\\\": {\\n    \\\"width\\\": 1440,\\n    \\\"height\\\": 960\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForSelector\\\",\\n      \\\"selector\\\": \\\"[data-testid='app-card']\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Storyteller\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Past sessions come first\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Hello from FastAPI!\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"screenshot\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n--- tools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-home-route.spec.json\\n{\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://localhost:8566\\\",\\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-20-home-route.png\\\",\\n  \\\"viewport\\\": {\\n    \\\"width\\\": 1440,\\n    \\\"height\\\": 960\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForSelector\\\",\\n      \\\"selector\\\": \\\"[data-testid='app-card']\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Past sessions come first\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Open sample workspace\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Past sessions now live on a real home route\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"screenshot\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n--- tools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-not-found-route.spec.json\\n{\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://localhost:8566/does-not-exist\\\",\\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-20-not-found-route.png\\\",\\n  \\\"viewport\\\": {\\n    \\\"width\\\": 1440,\\n    \\\"height\\\": 960\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForSelector\\\",\\n      \\\"selector\\\": \\\"[data-testid='not-found']\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Page not found\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"/does-not-exist\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"screenshot\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n--- tools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-session-route.spec.json\\n{\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"http://localhost:8566/sessions/moonlit-harbor\\\",\\n  \\\"outputPath\\\": \\\"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-20-session-route.png\\\",\\n  \\\"viewport\\\": {\\n    \\\"width\\\": 1440,\\n    \\\"height\\\": 960\\n  },\\n  \\\"steps\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"waitForSelector\\\",\\n      \\\"selector\\\": \\\"[data-testid='workspace-route']\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Session moonlit-harbor\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"/sessions/moonlit-harbor\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"assertText\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Chat lane\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"action\\\": \\\"screenshot\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nprompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:77:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_40\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’ve got enough context to narrow the implementation. The cleanest version of prompt 22 is a small full-stack slice: add a session detail endpoint, consume that snapshot on the workspace route, then rebuild the page into a real header plus responsive chat/main panes rather than a static placeholder.\"}}\nprompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:123:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_64\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '220,420p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"        </article>\\n      </div>\\n    </section>\\n  )\\n}\\n\\nfunction WorkspaceErrorState({\\n  errorMessage,\\n  sessionId,\\n}: {\\n  errorMessage: string\\n  sessionId: string\\n}) {\\n  return (\\n    <section\\n      className=\\\"workspace-page\\\"\\n      aria-label={`Session workspace for ${sessionId}`}\\n    >\\n      <article className=\\\"panel empty-state\\\">\\n        <p className=\\\"eyebrow\\\">Session workspace</p>\\n        <h1>Workspace unavailable</h1>\\n        <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">{errorMessage}</p>\\n        <Link className=\\\"ghost-link\\\" to={routePaths.home}>\\n          Return home\\n        </Link>\\n      </article>\\n    </section>\\n  )\\n}\\n\\nexport function SessionWorkspacePage() {\\n  const { sessionId = 'unknown-session' } = useParams()\\n  const [snapshot, setSnapshot] = useState<SessionSnapshot | null>(null)\\n  const [loadState, setLoadState] = useState<WorkspaceLoadState>('loading')\\n  const [errorMessage, setErrorMessage] = useState<string | null>(null)\\n\\n  useEffect(() => {\\n    let isDisposed = false\\n\\n    setLoadState('loading')\\n    setSnapshot(null)\\n    setErrorMessage(null)\\n\\n    void fetchSessionSnapshot(sessionId)\\n      .then((nextSnapshot) => {\\n        if (isDisposed) {\\n          return\\n        }\\n\\n        setSnapshot(nextSnapshot)\\n        setLoadState('ready')\\n      })\\n      .catch((error: unknown) => {\\n        if (isDisposed) {\\n          return\\n        }\\n\\n        if (\\n          error instanceof Error &&\\n          error.message.includes('Unexpected status code: 404')\\n        ) {\\n          setErrorMessage(\\n            `The session ${sessionId} could not be found in the durable store.`,\\n          )\\n        } else {\\n          setErrorMessage(\\n            'The workspace could not load this session right now. Try again once the backend is reachable.',\\n          )\\n        }\\n\\n        setLoadState('error')\\n      })\\n\\n    return () => {\\n      isDisposed = true\\n    }\\n  }, [sessionId])\\n\\n  if (loadState === 'loading') {\\n    return <WorkspaceLoadingState sessionId={sessionId} />\\n  }\\n\\n  if (loadState === 'error' || snapshot === null) {\\n    return (\\n      <WorkspaceErrorState\\n        errorMessage={\\n          errorMessage ?? 'The workspace could not load this session right now.'\\n        }\\n        sessionId={sessionId}\\n      />\\n    )\\n  }\\n\\n  const currentStage =\\n    snapshot.stage_states.find(\\n      (stage) => stage.stage === snapshot.current_stage,\\n    ) ??\\n    ({\\n      stage: snapshot.current_stage,\\n      label: getStageLabel(snapshot.current_stage),\\n      description: '',\\n      status: snapshot.overall_status,\\n    } as SessionStageStateView)\\n  const currentStageStatus = getStatusChipCopy(currentStage.status)\\n  const overallStatus = getStatusChipCopy(snapshot.overall_status)\\n  const progress = buildProgressCopy(snapshot)\\n  const chatPreview = buildChatPreview(snapshot)\\n\\n  return (\\n    <section\\n      className=\\\"workspace-page\\\"\\n      aria-label={`Session workspace for ${snapshot.display_title}`}\\n    >\\n      <header className=\\\"panel workspace-topbar\\\">\\n        <div className=\\\"workspace-topbar__copy\\\">\\n          <p className=\\\"eyebrow\\\">Session workspace</p>\\n          <h1>{snapshot.display_title}</h1>\\n          <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">\\n            Chat and stage-driven workflow controls now share one persistent\\n            surface, with the left lane reserved for conversation and the right\\n            canvas reserved for structured editing.\\n          </p>\\n        </div>\\n\\n        <dl className=\\\"workspace-topbar__status\\\" aria-label=\\\"Session status\\\">\\n          <div className=\\\"workspace-topbar__status-card\\\">\\n            <dt>Current stage</dt>\\n            <dd>\\n              <span className={currentStageStatus.className}>\\n                {currentStage.label}\\n              </span>\\n            </dd>\\n          </div>\\n          <div className=\\\"workspace-topbar__status-card\\\">\\n            <dt>Save status</dt>\\n            <dd>{formatSavedAt(snapshot.updated_at)}</dd>\\n          </div>\\n          <div className=\\\"workspace-topbar__status-card\\\">\\n            <dt>Session ID</dt>\\n            <dd>{snapshot.id}</dd>\\n          </div>\\n        </dl>\\n\\n        <div className=\\\"workspace-topbar__actions\\\">\\n          <span className={overallStatus.className}>{overallStatus.label}</span>\\n          <Link className=\\\"ghost-link\\\" to={routePaths.home}>\\n            Return home\\n          </Link>\\n        </div>\\n      </header>\\n\\n      <div className=\\\"workspace-shell\\\" data-testid=\\\"workspace-route\\\">\\n        <aside className=\\\"panel workspace-pane workspace-pane--chat\\\">\\n          <div className=\\\"pane-heading\\\">\\n            <div>\\n              <h2>Chat lane</h2>\\n              <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">\\n                Compact messages, action echoes, and interruption controls stay\\n                visible while the workflow advances.\\n              </p>\\n            </div>\\n            <span className=\\\"status-chip\\\">Chat bridge</span>\\n          </div>\\n\\n          <ol\\n            className=\\\"workspace-chat-list\\\"\\n            aria-label=\\\"Workspace chat preview\\\"\\n          >\\n            {chatPreview.map((entry) => (\\n              <li\\n                key={entry.id}\\n                className={`workspace-chat-message workspace-chat-message--${entry.speaker}`}\\n              >\\n                <span className=\\\"workspace-chat-message__speaker\\\">\\n                  {entry.speaker}\\n                </span>\\n                <p>{entry.body}</p>\\n              </li>\\n            ))}\\n          </ol>\\n\\n          <div className=\\\"workspace-chat-footer\\\">\\n            <strong>Composer dock</strong>\\n            <p>\\n              Message input, quick action chips, and live agent summaries will\\n              anchor here in the next workflow prompts.\\n            </p>\\n          </div>\\n        </aside>\\n\\n        <section className=\\\"panel workspace-pane workspace-pane--canvas\\\">\\n          <div className=\\\"pane-heading\\\">\\n            <div>\\n              <h2>Workflow canvas</h2>\\n              <p className=\\\"body-copy\\\">\\n                The main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and\\n                later composition or audio progress views.\\n              </p>\\n            </div>\\n            <span className={currentStageStatus.className}>\\n              {currentStageStatus.label}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nprompts/22-workspace-two-pane-layout.codex.jsonlines:150:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_80\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"docker compose -f infra/compose/docker-compose.yml run --rm browser node --input-type=module - <<'EOF'\\nimport fs from 'node:fs/promises';\\nimport puppeteer from 'puppeteer';\\n\\nconst snapshot = {\\n  id: 'moonlit-harbor',\\n  display_title: 'Lanterns Over Juniper Lake',\\n  working_title: 'Lanterns Over Juniper Lake',\\n  current_stage: 'beats',\\n  resume_stage: 'beats',\\n  furthest_completed_stage: 'characters',\\n  overall_status: 'in_progress',\\n  created_at: '2026-04-01T03:00:00Z',\\n  updated_at: '2026-04-01T05:15:00Z',\\n  completed_at: null,\\n  selected_genre: { id: 'genre-1', slug: 'quest-fantasy', label: 'Quest Fantasy' },\\n  selected_tone_profile: { id: 'tone-1', slug: 'hushed-wonder', label: 'Hushed Wonder' },\\n  progress: { total_stages: 10, completed_stages: 5, in_progress_stages: 1, needs_regeneration_stages: 0 },\\n  stage_states: [\\n    { stage: 'genre', label: 'Genre', description: 'Choose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Accepted quest fantasy.' },\\n    { stage: 'tone', label: 'Tone', description: 'Choose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Selected a soft adventurous tone.' },\\n    { stage: 'brief', label: 'Story brief', description: \\\\\\\"Capture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\\\\\\\", status: 'completed', detail: 'Accepted normalized brief.' },\\n    { stage: 'pitches', label: 'Pitches', description: 'Generate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Accepted the harbor lantern pitch.' },\\n    { stage: 'characters', label: 'Characters', description: 'Define the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.', status: 'completed', detail: 'Locked the character sheet.' },\\n    { stage: 'beats', label: 'Beat sheet', description: 'Store the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.', status: 'in_progress', detail: 'Midpoint needs one more bedti