{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_136","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented and checkpointed in commit `12351c2` (`feat(prompt-35): chat commands and quick actions`). The workspace now has a shared command layer for quick-action chips and slash commands, wired through the existing chat-intent endpoint and policy engine instead of a parallel path. The main additions are the command mapper in [chatCommands.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/chat/chatCommands.ts), explicit-command support in [intent_parser.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/intent_parser.py), and the chat-pane/workspace wiring in [SessionChatPane.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.tsx) and [SessionWorkspacePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx).\n\nVerification passed with targeted frontend tests, frontend build/lint, backend pytest, Ruff, and live browser QA. I captured desktop and mobile screenshots at [chat-commands-workspace.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/chat-commands-workspace.png) and [chat-commands-mobile.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/chat-commands-mobile.png). The required reviewer summary is written at [35-chat-commands-and-quick-actions.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/35-chat-commands-and-quick-actions.summary.md). One important limit remains: non-navigation quick actions still stop at proposal/policy evaluation, because the existing workspace only auto-applies preview/navigation actions. Browser QA also needed a temporary backend container workaround because the normal Compose `backend` service is failing on an unrelated local `secrets.yaml` schema mismatch."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"todo_list","items":[{"text":"Inspect current chat, action schema, policy engine, and workspace UI to find extension points for commands and quick actions","completed":true},{"text":"Implement shared command-to-action mapping and wire chat/slash command handling through existing action pipeline","completed":true},{"text":"Add discoverable quick action UI in chat/workspace and ensure stage-aware relevance","completed":true},{"text":"Add or update automated tests for command parsing and action dispatch behavior","completed":true},{"text":"Run targeted validation: tests, type/build checks, and browser-based UI verification with screenshots","completed":true},{"text":"Write final reviewer summary markdown file after verification is complete","completed":false}]}}
